paragraphs.text: Looking into the eyes of someone else and seeing pure love and acceptance being reflected back at us is as close as I can imagine we can get to looking into the eyes of God.
paragraphs.name: 5edb

paragraphs.text:
I am not who I think I am. 
I am not who you think I am. 
I am who I think you think I am.
paragraphs.name: 3b78

paragraphs.text: P.S. I typically don’t do this kind of thing, but I’ve come across a person, Jennifer Marie Gady. She’s one of a countless number of people who could use a set of loving eyes. She’s a beautiful soul and a passionate, poetic writer. The kind we need in this world to bring others across the bridge, because she’s crossing hers right now.
paragraphs.name: 881c

paragraphs.text:
Not to try to fix or heal them. 
Just to love them.
paragraphs.name: ff0d

paragraphs.text: It’s your perception of other people’s perception about you that creates your identity as a human. So, you are who you think OTHERS think you are.
